The President has nominated James R. Sweeney II, an Indianapolis attorney, to fill a judicial emergency on the United States District Court for the Southern District of Indiana. There are currently 64 judicial emergencies in various states across the country. If confirmed, Sweeney will serve as a District Judge in Indiana. Sweeney is a partner at Barnes & Thornburg, LLP and has extensive experience in federal contracting, procurement, and national security. He has also served as a law clerk to judges in the Sixth Circuit Court of Appeals and the Southern District of Indiana. Prior to his legal career, Sweeney served in the United States Marine Corps for 11 years. He holds a B.S. from the United States Naval Academy and a J.D. from Notre Dame Law School. Vice President Mike Pence has praised Sweeney's nomination and called for swift confirmation hearings.